    h1#projects Projects
    hr

    div.wrapper#seed
        section.row.container-fluid
            span.col-md-6
                img(src="images/SIMInsight.png" style="width:100%")
            span.col-md-6
                article
                    h1 SEED: A SIM-Based Solution to 5G Failures
                    p We devise a novel SIM-based solution to 5G failure diagnosis and handling. Our work <i>"SEED: A SIM-Based Solution to 5G Failures"</i> has been appeared in ACM SIGCOMM 2022.
                        a(href="docs/SEED-A SIM-Based Solution to 5G Failures.pdf" target="_blank") &nbsp;[PDF]

    div.wrapper.shadow#secureSIM
        section.row.container-fluid
            span.col-md-4
                img(src="images/securesim.png" style="width:80%")
            span.col-md-8
                article
                    h1 SecureSIM
                    p We uncover new vulnerabilities of the current SIM practice and propose a new solution that offers both authentication and fine-grained access control. Our work <i>"SecureSIM: Rethinking Authentication and Access Control for SIM/eSIM"</i> has been appeared in the 27th Annual International Conference On Mobile Computing And Networking &nbsp;
                        a(href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3447993.3483254" target="_blank") (MobiCom'21). &nbsp;
                        a(href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1145/3447993.3483254" target="_blank") [PDF]

    div.wrapper#sonica
        section.row.container-fluid
            span.col-md-4
                article
                    h1 Sonica
                    p Sonica (Software-defined Open NB-IoT Research Platform) provides an open-source NB-IoT testbed that is able to communicate with commodity off-the-shelf (COTS) devices.
                    a.btn-lg.btn-success(href="https://github.com/sonica-nbiot/sonica" target="_blank") View on Github
            span.col-md-8
                img(src="images/sonica-overview.png" style="width:100%")

    div.wrapper#flora
        section.row.container-fluid
            span.col-md-8
                img(src="images/flora_intro.png" style="width:100%")
            span.col-md-4
                article
                    h1 Flora
                    p Flora (Flexible Mobile Network Platform) is a flexible software-defined 4G LTE/5G system without commodity SIM cards, communication chipsets, or dedicated infrastructure equipment.
                    a.btn-lg.btn-success(href="https://project-flora.github.io/Flora/" target="_blank") View on Github

    div.wrapper.shadow#lrp
        section.row.container-fluid
            span.col-md-12
                img(src="images/LRP.png" style="width:100%")
            span.col-md-12
                article
                    h1 Mobile VR System with Cellular Latency Reduction
                    p <i><strong>Device-Based LTE Latency Reduction at the Application Layer</strong></i> appeared in the 18th USENIX Symposium on Networked Systems Design and Implementation &nbsp;
                        a(href="https://www.usenix.org/system/files/nsdi21-tan.pdf") (NSDI '21).
                    //a.btn-lg.btn-success(href="https://project-flora.github.io/Flora/" target="_blank") View on Github

